The crystal orbital overlap population (COHP) was developed to visualize energy-resolved chemical bonding for solids, by partitioning the band structure energy into contributions from each orbital pair30. Following the tight-binding model as given in Eqs. 2 and 3, the COHP can be defined as:4COHP= ∑iα,jβciα*cjβ⟨φiα∣Ĥ∣φjβ⟩\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
